activeYears.title: active years
activeYears.description: Also called"floruit". Use this if the active years are in one field that can't be split. Else use activeYearsStartYear and activeYearsEndYear

allegiance.title: allegiance
allegiance.description: The country or other power the person served. Multiple countries may be indicated together with the corresponding dates. This field should not be used to indicate a particular service branch, which is better indicated by the branch field.

awardName.title: awardName
awardName.description: Award a person has received &#40;literal). Compare to award (ObjectProperty)

bustWaistHipSize.title: bust-waist-hip Size
bustWaistHipSize.description: Use this property if all 3 sizes are given together &#40;DBpedia cannot currently extract 3 Lengths out of a field). Otherwise use separate fields bustSize, waistSize, hipSize

handedness.title: handedness
handedness.description: an attribute of humans defined by their unequal distribution of fine motor skill between the left and right hands.

individualisedPnd.title: individualised PND number
individualisedPnd.description: PND &#40;Personennamendatei) data about a person. PND is published by the German National Library. For each person there is a record with her/his name, birth and occupation connected with a unique identifier, the PND number.

significantProject.title: significant project
significantProject.description: A siginificant artifact constructed by the person.
